cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.SI

The paper deals with the application of neural networks to predict human behavior in repeated strategic interactions. This involves learning from a dataset of normal-form games from experiments with human participants. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development and application of algorithms that enable computers to learn from data. The paper also involves game theory and decision-making, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the use of neural networks for prediction tasks falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the economic value of the predictions, which could place it under cs.CE (Computational Economics). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of sequences of actions, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
